FuncDef: This command sets the tunnel-id range that is used to allocate a new tunnel-id for a tunnel for which multi-chassis redundancy is configured to this MCS peer.

ParaDef.Info: Specifies the start of the range of L2TP tunnel identifiers that can be allocated by L2TP on this system, to be synchronized with Multi Chassis Redundancy Synchronization (MCS). Values-1 to 16383.
Specifies the end of the range of L2TP tunnel identifiers that can be allocated by L2TP on this system, to be synchronized with Multi Chassis Redundancy Synchronization (MCS). Values-1 to 16383.
